Wait, looking at the API code more carefully - the ORPC error handler at line 136-143 of `index.ts`:
```typescript
if (response.status >= 500) {
    const body = await response.clone().text();
    logger.error("RPC error on {path}: {status} {body}", {
        path: url.pathname,
        status: response.status,
        body,
    });
}
```

This only logs the response body, not the original error. The ClickHouse error for `developers/sessions` was logged separately because it's an unhandled error that Bun prints to stderr. So for `projects/investment`, the error is probably being caught by ORPC's error handler before it propagates to stderr, which means the original error details are lost. I should add a try/catch in the handler itself to capture and log the actual error.

